It should be possible to interact with the scheme environment either
through (:internal) functions or through a library.

Having first class environments makes it possible to write even more
functions in libraries.

For ideas, look at e.g.
http://groups.csail.mit.edu/mac/ftpdir/6.001-fall91/ps9/ps9-ports.scm

or see how they do it in the T programming language.
